The People of the State of New York ex rel. Frederick Boutelle, Appellant, v Edward O’Mara, as Superintendent of Wallkill Correctional Facility, Respondent. Submitted February 28, 1977; decided April 5, 1977

Reported below, 55 AD2d 804.

Motion for leave to appeal dismissed upon the ground that relator has been released on parole and, therefore, his liberty is no longer restrained to such a decree as to entitle him to the extraordinary writ of habeas corpus (People ex rel. Wilder v Markley, 26 NY2d 648).
